# No-Go Rules

The following choices are explicitly prohibited unless the user explicitly asks for them in writing.

## Frameworks & runtime

- Do NOT introduce Next.js. Astro is the only static-site framework.
- Do NOT introduce a database.
- Do NOT connect a Headless CMS.
- Do NOT use Tailwind or any utility-CSS framework.

## Repo & CI

- Do NOT create GitHub Actions. Builds run on Cloudflare Pages Git Integration.
- Do NOT use Gitee.

## File layout

- Do NOT place Cloudflare Functions under `apps/site-builder/functions`. They live at the repo root `functions/` only.
- Do NOT let Astro (`apps/site-builder`) read `sites/` directly. It reads only `apps/site-builder/.generated/`.
- Do NOT manually edit `apps/site-builder/.generated/`. It is produced by build scripts and must remain regenerable.
- Do NOT treat `dist/` as source. It is build output and is wiped on every build.

## Themes & content

- Do NOT hardcode real company names, logos, navigation labels, emails, phone numbers, or marketing copy inside `packages/theme-*` or `apps/site-builder` components.
- Do NOT write per-site CSS inside a theme package. Site-level visual differentiation must flow through `site.config.ts` data only.
